        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the onion is softening, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> dried oregano</strong>,<strong> balsamic vinegar </strong>and<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
